JSopX™ Asp.NET Core

JSopX™ Asp.NET Core

From the ﻿BETA v 2025 Jason Silvestri Open Project EXperiences (JSopX™) Collection

The JSopX™ Asp.NET Core Project is a FREE, open-source demonstration project built in Visual Studio, code named, JSopX.AspNetCore. It showcases the transformation of an existing ASP.NET Core application—complete with its own assets, Web APIs, and standards—into a scalable solution for optimal enterprise application migration.

JSopX™ Asp.NET Core Project

The JSopX™ Asp.NET Core Project addresses several high-level business concerns, not only shown through design patterns and best practices within its own JSopX™ Project ecosystem, but ultimately as it evolves into a valuable project component of the Jason Silvestri Open Project EXperiences (JSopX™) Enterprise Application too.

By aligning varied frameworks—ranging from ASP.NET Core to Angular, Vue, React, Blazor, MAUI and more, all using the same Web API, assets, documentation, and standards—these projects create a consistent development landscape where code can be shared, extended, and integrated seamlessly, bridging-of-the-critical-gap, between front-end dynamism and back-end security.


Previous Next

Simulating an Existing Project

We initially create the JSopX™ Asp.NET Core Project to simulate an "Existing" Server-side Apps Example Weather Forecast Asp.NET Core application, with its own Web API and existing standards, to conform to the initial business requirements set forth by the fictional stakeholders.

Previous Next

Create Our Development Standards

JSopX™ Enterprise application development isn't just about writing code—it's about creating scalable, maintainable, and secure solutions that stand the test of time. This takes a series of disciplines that provide the framework for sustainable success, ensuring every project delivers efficiency, performance, and an exceptional developer experience.

The biggest mistake businesses and developers make is not following some form of development standards, but not me, and not you.

Previous Next

Multi-Platform
Creative Standards

A visually inconsistent application creates confusion. Every JSopX™ project must maintain standardized UI/UX elements. We quickly design and customize multi-platform, web, desktop & native mobile applications, using Bootstrap v 5.3, which we then extend as we go by creating RCLs (Razor Class Libraries).

Previous Next

Using Object-Oriented Programming (OOP)

Enterprise applications must be modular, reusable, and scalable using Object-Oriented Programming (OOP). We create Classes, RCLs, Web APIs, and other Resource Libraries, sharing resources across the JSopX™ ecosystem seamlessly. More rewarding, because we put the work in up front with developing & following standards, developers get to work on cooler things they are more passionate about too, like Feature Highlights.

Previous Next

We Get to Extend Existing Project

As the project evolves through each Lifecycle Phase, we extend the application by creating new user interfaces, such as dashboards, logins, registration, in addition to being able to apply the standardized assets and resources we took the time to develop, implement security and writing documentation a well oiled machine and team relies on, and more!

We Become A Functioning Project of the JSopX™ Enterprise Solution

The seamless integration into an enterprise-level application, adopting standardized Web API access, design patterns, and shared resources across the ecosystem.

JSopX™ Asp.NET Core Project Dependencies

JSopX™ Asp.NET Core Project leverages other project dependencies anywhere we can do better to scale resources, assets and data end points. The primary project suite dependencies are as follows:

JSopX.ClassLibrary

The JSopX™ Class Library Project EXperience is used to leverage common properties and values, largely static, that are common across all projects.

JSopX.RCLxProper

The JSopX™ RCL x Proper Razor Class Library Project EXperience is a production-ready Razor Class Library offering structured components, pages, and views.

JSopX.WebAPI

The JSopX™ Web API Project EXperience is a RESTful API backend that ties the ecosystem together, by providing consistent endpoints and data services.

Previous Next

JSopX™ Multi-Platform
Bootstrap RCLs

You can quickly design and customize JSopX™ multi-platform, web, desktop & native mobile applications, using JSopX™ Multi-Platform Bootstrap RCLs (Razor Class Libraries). The world's most popular front-end open source toolkit, meets the world's most caring lead developer friend you'll ever have, to bring you Bootstrap v 5.3 features like Sass variables, mixins, responsive flex & grid systems, with the combined JSopX™ RCL support of extensive prebuilt components & themes for all projects, including Asp.NET Core, Blazor, MAUI, Angular, React, Vue and more!

JSopX™ Development Standards

JSopX™ Enterprise application development isn't just about writing code—it's about creating scalable, maintainable, and secure solutions that stand the test of time. This takes a series of disciplines that provide the framework for sustainable success, ensuring every project delivers efficiency, performance, and an exceptional developer experience. The JSopX™ Asp.NET Core Project was made possible, thanks to these JSopX™ disciplines.

Security-First Approach

Security isn’t optional—it's a requirement. Every project must implement proactive security measures at all levels.

Performance & Caching

A fast app is a usable app. Sometimes what's best isn't obvious. Every application must be optimized for speed and efficiency.

Documentation & Code Readability

Code that isn’t documented doesn’t exist. Every project must include clear, structured documentation for developers and stakeholders.

Centralized API & Data Flow

A single, unified API strategy is critical for data consistency, maintainability, scalability & security, as it is about accessibility & data integrity.

UI/UX Consistency & Creative Design

A visually inconsistent application creates confusion. Every JSopX™ project must maintain standardized UI/UX elements.

Multi-Platform Compatibility

JSopX™ projects must work seamlessly across multiple platforms, include web, desktop and native mobile user experiences.

Open-Source & Free Accessibility

Custom to the JSopX™ product suite, JSopX™ follows an open-source-first philosophy—no hidden fees, no locked features.

Object-Oriented Programming

Enterprise applications must be modular, reusable, and scalable using Object-Oriented Programming (OOP).

The harsh reality is that it doesn't matter whether you are a startup or a Fortune 500 company. If you have a few or many applications—you are building enterprise solutions.
